<h2 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-RAID-Ris=
k,Assumptions,IssuesandDependencies">RAID - Risk, Assumptions, Issues and D=
ependencies</h2>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-Assumpti=
ons">Assumptions</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped relative-table confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 93.=
9241%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 4.94948%;">
<col style=3D"width: 42.7455%;">
<col style=3D"width: 52.305%;">
</colgroup>
<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Ref #</p></th>
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Assumption</p></th>
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A01</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Redirected account closure</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Account closure is a <strong>manual process</strong> that requires canc=
ellation of any redirections <strong>before</strong> the source or target a=
ccount is closed.</li>
<li>From the <strong>Channel</strong> perspective:=20
<ul>
<li>It is assumed that the <strong>Account WASH API</strong> will return <s=
trong>no redirection configuration</strong> if the account is closed.</li>
<li><strong>No logic</strong> will be implemented on the Channel side to ha=
ndle redirection during account closure.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A02</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Transaction posting on the source account</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>If redirection is configured in <strong>10x,&nbsp;</strong>
<ul>
<li>The expected behavior from business requirement is:=20
<ul>
<li>The <strong>transaction is posted to the target account</strong>.</li>
<li>A <strong>zero-value non-financial transaction</strong> is posted to th=
e source account.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>It is known that <strong>10x currently only posts to the target account=
</strong>, not the source.</li>
<li>From the Channel perspective:=20
<ul>
<li>There is <strong>no impact</strong> on whether the source account trans=
action is displayed, as it originates from <strong>ATLAS</strong>.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A03</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Narrative for redirected fees/interests</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p=
></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Metadata from <strong>10x</strong> may be <strong>insufficient</strong>=
 to formulate a complete narrative for source/target accounts.</li>
<li>Alternatively, it may require <strong>significant effort from ATLAS</st=
rong> to combine data from multiple events.</li>
<li>From the Channel perspective:=20
<ul>
<li>There is <strong>no impact</strong> on whether the narrative is display=
ed, as it originates from <strong>ATLAS</strong>.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A04</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Fees display on channels&nbsp;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Fees are displayed at the <strong>transactional level</strong>.</li>
<li>Transactional data originates from <strong>ATLAS</strong>.</li>
<li>The <strong>rate of fees</strong> is static and sourced from the <stron=
g>WASH/10x endpoint</strong>.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A05</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Limitation on number of redirection to be displayed / set up</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"efdccad2-cf53-45b3-9b=
77-e8ee39a215bf">Redirection limit (if any) should be applied at the source=
 system, i.e. 10x</span></li>
<li>No limit will be set up in channel to control display of the redirectio=
n configuration.</li>
<li>Assume all the redirection data can be displayed in a single page witho=
ut any pagination.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-Constrai=
nts&amp;Dependencies">Constraints &amp; Dependencies</h3>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 364.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 372.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 480.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 361.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 184.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Ref #</st=
rong></p><p>[C-###, D-###]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Considera=
tions Type</strong></p><p>[Constraints, Dependencies]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Descripti=
on</strong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Notes</st=
rong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Date</str=
ong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-JIRAFEATURE-001=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Unused limit fees=
/<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Line Fee dependency</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>The fees introduced in this feature have a <strong>strong business depe=
ndency</strong> on the <strong>Overdraft/Facility endpoint</strong>.</li>
<li>Any decision to <strong>decouple</strong> these fees from the Overdraft=
/Facility endpoint will introduce <strong>complexity</strong> to the upstre=
am integration.</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-10-22" class=3D"date-past">22 Oct 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-JIRAFEATURE-002=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Limitation on the=
 GTS interest API</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Refer to Key Decision #002 from&nbsp;<br><a href=3D"https://confluence.=
srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/08.+SD%3A+Interest+and+Tax+Summary" rel=3D"=
nofollow">08. SD: Interest and Tax Summary - Westpac One Core - Westpac Ent=
erprise Confluence</a></li>
<li>or&nbsp;</li>
<li>Open item 01 in&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/d=
isplay/ARTC/76518+-+ACD+for+Account+Balance+as+at+a+Past+Date#id-76518ACDfo=
rAccountBalanceasataPastDate-OpenItems" rel=3D"nofollow">76518 - ACD for Ac=
count Balance as at a Past Date - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Con=
fluence</a></li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-10-23" class=3D"date-past">23 Oct 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-JIRAFEATURE-003=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint&nbsp;<=
/p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Limitation on Fee=
s related</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>As Per the ACD, the following limitations applies on 10x level. It will =
only impact Channels on a testing level, and no handling is required.&nbsp;=
</p>
<p>1. 10x can't support Line fee for IDOL.</p>
<p>2. It can be determined at an Account (subscription) level whether an Ar=
ranged Overdraft or IDOL exists for that Account. However, it cannot be det=
ermined which one the Fee was for.</p>
<p>3. on a transaction level, we can't tell if the Fees whether it is a "Li=
ne Fee" or "Unused Limit Fee" since 10x didn't emit this as an event to ATL=
AS.&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-11-07" class=3D"date-past">07 Nov 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>D-JIRAFEATURE-001=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Decision on the F=
ees / redirection endpoint&nbsp;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>A decision is required from <strong><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user=
-mention" data-username=3D"M037818" href=3D"/display/~M037818" data-linked-=
resource-id=3D"7244962" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-reso=
urce-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.=
au">Stuart Murdoch</a> </strong>to confirm:</p>
<ul>
<li>Whether <strong>Fees / Redirection information</strong> from <strong>WA=
SH/10x</strong> will be retrieved via:=20
<ul>
<li>The <strong>w1c Arrangement API</strong>, or</li>
<li>The <strong>w1c Facility API</strong></li>
<li>Another new endpoint</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Confirmed for Fees we are going to re-use <strong>w1c Facility API&nbsp;=
</strong>or directly calling <strong>WASH Facility API&nbsp;</strong>(refer=
 to Key decision #001)</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-10-22" class=3D"date-past">22 Oct 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>D-JIRAFEATURE-002=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency on ATL=
AS</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>ATLAS is depending on the 10x uplift / documentation for the source acco=
unt posting.</p>
<p>The impact to Channels will be an uncertainty on the source account "non=
-financial transaction" handling when data is returned by the ATLAS.&nbsp;<=
br>
 The displaying logic will be depending on the ATLAS solution design</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2026-03-04" class=3D"date-past">04 Mar 2026</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>D-JIRAFEATURE-003=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency on WAS=
H / 10x</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>in 10x/WASH, new Enum need to be added to distinguish Credit and Debit i=
nterest redirection.</p>
<p>The value of the Enum still pending for confirmation.&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2026-03-04" class=3D"date-past">04 Mar 2026</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-KeyDecis=
ions"><span>Key Decisions</span></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped relative-table confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 97.=
3903%;">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 2.70424%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 11.597%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 71.0398%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 11.389%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 3.27629%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Ref</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Decision</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh"><p>Description</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Decision made by</p>
</div></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Status</th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#001</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Fees configuration endpoints&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<ul>
<li style=3D"list-style-type: none;">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>The new fee endpoint is to be served by the new W1C Facility cap API, i=
f not available it will be sourced from the WASH directly for the interim.<=
/li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);"><span class=3D"confluence-embedded=
-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-emb=
