<h2 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-Technica=
lDebt">Technical Debt</h2>
<p></p>
<p>N/A</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-Solution=
"><span>Solution</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"id-13.SD:Fees,Interest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-Solution=
Overview"><span>Solution Overview</span></h2>
<p>This change introduces enhancements to the Customer Portal to improve vi=
sibility of interest and fee-related transactions. It enables customers to =
view redirected interest and fee transactions on the charge account=E2=80=
=99s transaction listing, and highlights redirection arrangements on the so=
urce account=E2=80=99s details page. Additionally, overdraft fees=E2=80=94i=
ncluding Unused Limit Fees and Line Fees=E2=80=94will be displayed with det=
ailed breakdowns on the Account Activity page, along with any applicable fe=
e refunds shown as transactions. These changes require updates to or creati=
on of EXP APIs and architectural input regarding the W1C arrangement.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Sto<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"a6faa42e-f50d-4e45-=
b548-b73ef94d472e">ry refers</span> to&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.s=
rv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D2182705430#id-13.SD:Fees,I=
nterest/FeeRedirectionsandCustomerRefunds-UserStoryTraceability" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">13. SD: Fees, Interest/Fee Redirections and Customer Refunds</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table id=3D"TBL1773175605616" class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTa=
ble" style=3D"width: 92.3957%;" data-snooker-col-series=3D"numbers" data-sn=
ooker-locked-cols=3D"0">
<colgroup>
